The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Sunday, February 08, 2004 				 Father-in-law arrested for dowry death
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								Krishnagar (Nadia), Feb. 7: Arot Sheikh, a farmer of Kachkali village in Nakashipara, was arrested today in connection with the death of his 20-year-old daughter-in-law. Jyotsna Bibis husband, Ator, is absconding.																								Jyotsna committed suicide by consuming poison last night. Police found Jyotsnas body in a banana grove close to her in-laws house early this morning.																								A suicide note was found tied to her sari, where Jyotsna alleged that she had to take the extreme step as she was unable to bear the torture by her husband and in-laws.																								Arot was arrested after Isub Sheikh, Jyotsnas father, lodged a complaint with the police. Isub said his daughter had to commit suicide as he failed to pay her in-laws dowry within the given time. 
